Journal.Title: Journal of medical and veterinary mycology : bi-monthly publication of the International Society for Human and Animal Mycology

Article.ArticleTitle: Environmental isolation of Cryptococcus neoformans var. gattii from Eucalyptus tereticornis.

AbstractText: As an extension of the previously established association between Cryptococcus neoformans var. gattii and Eucalyptus camaldulensis (River red gum) we have now found a similar relationship between C. neoformans var. gattii and the closely related Eucalyptus tereticornis (Forest red gum). The global distribution of E. tereticornis is similar to that of E. camaldulensis.
